# ML dependencies — INTENT file.
#
# Not required for paper / live trading. The ml/ modules import
# these lazily and fail open when any one is missing, so a
# paper-only deploy can skip the ML install entirely.
#
# Edit this file, then run:
#
#   make compile-deps
#
# That recompiles requirements-ml.txt with full transitive deps +
# sha256 hashes via ``pip-compile --generate-hashes``. Commit BOTH
# this file and the generated requirements-ml.txt.
#
# Audit v26-26: ``-c requirements.txt`` pins every shared transitive
# dependency (numpy, pandas, scipy, etc.) to the same versions as
# the core install. Without this constraint, pip-compile can resolve
# a newer numpy for the ML side, which causes runtime
# incompatibilities when the ML subsystem runs in the same process
# as the paper engine. The constraint applies BOTH at compile time
# (pip-compile honours it when resolving versions) AND at install
# time (the operator should install requirements.txt first; pip
# refuses to downgrade a package already at the constrained
# version).
-c requirements.txt

lightgbm==4.6.0
llvmlite==0.44.0
numba==0.61.2
scikit-learn==1.8.0
scipy==1.17.1
xgboost==3.2.0
